Go to temp folder:

cd /tmp

Then

curl -O https://repo.anaconda.com/archive/Anaconda3-2020.11-Linux-x86_64.sh

(You should perform the checksum of the dowloaded file)

Start!

bash Anaconda3-2020.11-Linux-x86_64.sh

It will start installing. When asks to prepend the install location to PATH type yes!

If you don't type yes you can change it at the end with this 2 lines:


eval "$(/home/as/anaconda3/bin/conda shell.bash hook)"

Conda init
